# Q-Periapt asserts byte-identical output across platforms, so the repository itself must
# check out byte-for-byte identically on every OS. Without this, Git's default autocrlf on
# Windows would rewrite LF->CRLF on checkout and silently mutate the vendored NIST/ACVP/
# X-Wing test vectors (and the C shim), breaking reproducibility of the very vectors the
# suite pins. Force LF for all text; never normalize the byte-sensitive vendored data.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Vendored reference/test vectors and reference data: byte-exact, no EOL conversion ever.
*.json -text
*.txt -text
